    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "One new key today, and then a proper workout. The slash is a small mark with steady work: it splits a date, a fraction, a path. After that you will run a full line that gathers every symbol you have learned - the at sign, the hash, the dollar, the percent, the brackets - in real copy."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The slash sits on the bottom row, to the right, with the question mark above it. Strike / with the right pinky, no Shift. It needs no Shift partner here - just a light, clean tap."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "keyboard",
      "title": "Even is faster",
      "text": "A paragraph of mixed symbols rewards rhythm, not speed. Hold a calm, even beat and the hard keys arrive on time. Lurch at them and you fumble. A little every day."
